XL.-1449, June 2. Grant from Hugh Monnke, of Notting- ham, shearman, to William Jonson, of the same, ironmonger, of a messuage on the southern side of the Saturday Market (‘ Forum Sabbati’>, between the tenements of Hugh Willughby, of Rysley, on both sides, which messuage Monnke lately had of the gift and feoffment of Robert Rasyn, of Nottingham, genffleman, and Alice his wife. VVitnesses: Thomas Thurland, Mayor‚ John Squer and Thomas Ivynet, Bailiffs,2 Thomas Alestre, John Plumptre‚ John Ilkeston, and Thomas Heth. 4466.
